вҠў original
  given text вүЎ "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog"
  yield word-count, longest-word, reversed

  вҲҙ Count the words in В«textВ», find the longest word,
    and reverse the entire string.

  вҠЁ word-count is a positive integer
  вҠЁ longest-word appears in В«textВ»
  вҠЁ reversed read backwards equals В«textВ»

вҠў factor
  given В§target
  yield cells[]

  вҲҙ Read В«В§targetВ». Split it into cells that each
    compute exactly one output.

  вҠЁ each cell in cells has exactly one yield
  вҠЁ composing cells reproduces В§target's behavior

вҠў run-factored
  given factor(В§original)вҶ’cells
  given text вүЎ "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog"
  yield word-count, longest-word, reversed

  вҲҙ Execute В«factorвҶ’cellsВ» in order with В«textВ» as input.
    Collect word-count, longest-word, and reversed.

  вҠЁ word-count = В«originalвҶ’word-countВ»
  вҠЁ longest-word = В«originalвҶ’longest-wordВ»
  вҠЁ reversed = В«originalвҶ’reversedВ»
